The paper deals with local problems in distributed computing, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The focus on bandwidth restrictions and the use of randomized and deterministic algorithms suggests that the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Algorithms (cs.AL) sub-categories may also be relevant. Finally, the use of tools such as bounded independence and conditional expectations suggests that the Network Information Theory (cs.NI) sub-category may also be applicable.
